<![CDATA[ <p style="text-align:left"><b>This is where you save and sustain lives </b></p><p style="text-align:inherit"></p><p style="text-align:left">At Baxter, we are deeply connected by our mission. No matter your role at Baxter, your work makes a positive impact on people around the world. You’ll feel a sense of purpose throughout the organization, as we know our work improves outcomes for millions of patients. </p><p style="text-align:inherit"></p><p style="text-align:left">Baxter’s products and therapies are found in almost every hospital worldwide, in clinics and in the home. For over 85 years, we have pioneered significant medical innovations that transform healthcare.</p><p style="text-align:inherit"></p><p style="text-align:left">Together, we create a place where we are happy, successful and inspire each other. This is where you can do your best work. </p><p style="text-align:inherit"></p><p style="text-align:left">Join us at the intersection of saving and sustaining lives— where your purpose accelerates our mission. </p><p style="text-align:inherit"></p><p style="text-align:inherit"></p><p><b>Your role at Baxter:</b></p><p></p><p>Directly supervises and supports a staff of employees assigned to various jobs such as receiving, shipping, customer orders, and/or replenishment. This position is responsible for ensuring that customer orders, complaints, and requests are processed in a timely, accurate, and efficient manner.</p><p></p><p><b>Your team:</b></p><p></p><p>We develop quality products with the patient in mind, so our marketing efforts are also patient centric. That means you can be proud of our work and the value we provide to people every day.</p><p></p><p>As a large, multinational organization, you could expand your knowledge through collaboration with a variety of individuals, exposure to different facets of our portfolio, and an encouraging leadership team that encourages ongoing development.</p><p></p><p><b>What you'll be doing:</b></p><ul><li>Supervise distribution of all products from the warehouse and employee workload as the need arises to optimize staff efficiency.</li><li>Develop and implement effective systems and procedures to ensure effectiveness and efficiency of the operation. Monitor warehouse services and settle the best methods to overcome obstacles while maintaining acceptable service levels.</li><li>Insure all new employees are accurately trained. Serve as customer concern point for employees with problems. Take proactive steps as appropriate.</li><li>Review and answer inquiries from customer service, customers, sales, vendors, and management. Use judgment and subtlety to handle complaints and resolve issues.</li><li>Responsible for implementing procedures to meet federal, state, company, and facility regulations. Coordinate and support all standard operating and quality procedures.</li><li>Assist in the supervision of product recalls, field corrective actions, and product returns.</li><li>May participate in budget and forecasting processes along with other projects as requested.</li><li>Must have excellent social skills both oral and written along with proven ability to implement change.</li><li>Must be able to prioritize and lead a number of ongoing issues, meet deadlines, and communicate with senior management.</li><li>Strong analytical skills and experience with spreadsheets and word processing applications required.</li></ul><p></p><p><b>What you'll bring:</b></p><ul><li>High School Diploma or GED required. Associate’s or Bachelor’s preferred.</li><li>Minimum 3-5 years of supervisory experience.</li><li>3+ years of experience in a distribution environment.</li><li>Experience Operating Powered Industrial Equipment, preferred.</li><li>Strong organizational, leadership and social skills.</li><li>Must be able to work independently.</li><li>Computer proficiency in Microsoft Office and the ability to use enterprise.</li><li>Must have excellent communication skills both oral and written along 